<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 8:26PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Bradley, western
Polk and southeastern Hamilton Counties through 1015 PM EDT...
At 926 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Harrison, or 9 miles northeast of Chattanooga, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Cleveland, Benton, Soddy-Daisy, Lakesite, South
Cleveland, Harrison, East Cleveland, Wildwood Lake and Collegedale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
